{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17598466","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17598466"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T11:38:54+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T11:38:54+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15476"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15476","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15476"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.47,0.17,0.2,0.03,0.13]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8167"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"61529"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8167","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8167"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15476"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"46982"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"11"},{"type":"tags","id":"14"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"1061"},{"type":"tags","id":"1758"},{"type":"tags","id":"2701"},{"type":"tags","id":"4927"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"8118"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19784"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19787"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"61529","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/61529"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 42-year-old man presents with chronic cough, fever, and large volumes of foul-smelling purulent sputum. His medical history includes previous tuberculosis with recurrent pneumonia. A chest X-ray demonstrates the characteristic \u0027tram track sign\u0027.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following pathological changes would most likely be present in the airways?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Airway dilation and scarring","Airspace enlargement and wall destruction","Inflammatory scarring with obliteration","Smooth muscle hyperplasia with inflammation","Mucous gland hyperplasia with hypersecretion"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient\u0027s presentation is consistent with bronchiectasis. The pathological hallmark is \u003Cstrong\u003Eairway dilation and scarring\u003C/strong\u003E of the bronchi. This occurs due to chronic inflammation and infection leading to permanent structural changes.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAirspace enlargement and wall destruction\u003C/strong\u003E is characteristic of emphysema. \u003Cstrong\u003EInflammatory scarring with obliteration\u003C/strong\u003E is seen in bronchiolitis obliterans. \u003Cstrong\u003ESmooth muscle hyperplasia with inflammation\u003C/strong\u003E is typical of asthma. \u003Cstrong\u003EMucous gland hyperplasia with hypersecretion\u003C/strong\u003E is found in chronic bronchitis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u0027tram track sign\u0027 represents parallel lines of thickened, dilated bronchial walls seen on chest X-ray, which is pathognomonic for bronchiectasis.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Bronchiectasis is characterized by permanent airway dilation and scarring, often presenting with chronic productive cough and recurrent infections","The \u0027tram track sign\u0027 on chest X-ray represents thickened, dilated bronchial walls viewed longitudinally"],"references":["Mason, R. J., Broaddus, V. C., Martin, T. R., King, T. E., Schraufnagel, D., Murray, J. F., \u0026 Nadel, J. A. (2010). Murray and Nadel\u0027s textbook of respiratory medicine E-book: 2-volume set. Elsevier Health Sciences","Bird K, Memon J. Bronchiectasis. [Updated 2023 May 22]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK430810/","O\u0027Donnell AE. Bronchiectasis - A Clinical Review. N Engl J Med. 2022 Aug 11;387(6):533-545. doi: 10.1056/NEJMra2202819. PMID: 35947710","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"46982"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15476"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"46982","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/46982"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-15T18:24:41+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-15T18:27:42+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8167"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"61529"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"11","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/11"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec1","name":"Respiratory Medicine","synonyms":["Pulmonology"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"14","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/14"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udda0","name":"Infectious Diseases","synonyms":["ID"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2021-05-21T07:51:58+09:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"t